%N A395404 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k)^4 + Omega(k)^4.
%C A395404 From _David A. Corneth_, Apr 23 2026: (Start)
%C A395404 Contains 20701*p^2 where p is prime and 20701, p coprime.
%C A395404 Contains 2628222*p^2 where p is prime and 2628222, p coprime.
%C A395404 Contains 2905790*p^2 where p is prime and 2905790, p coprime.
%C A395404 Contains 3853096509 = 3*1087^3 via 29349 = 3^3*1087.
%C A395404 Hence the sequence is infinite. (End)
%e A395404 29349 is a term since sigma(29349) = 43520 = 39168 + 8^4 + 4^4 = psi(29349) + tau(29349)^4 + Omega(29349)^4.
%o A395404 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f)^4 + bigomega(f)^4; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 21 2026
